docs.title: All about me
docs.text:
Cullen (He/They) is a data analyst and programmer based in Portland, Oregon. He focuses on projects using Python, R, and SQL.

He enjoys solving complex problems and researching new understanding.

Cullen is also an audio engineer that has worked in theatre, recording, and live music.

His hobbies include painting and modeling miniatures, tabletop roleplaying, playing bass, and cooking. He also enjoys spending time with his animals, Socks and Ludwig.

docs.title: Bicycle Share Case Study:
docs.text:
Cleaned, processed, analyzed and reported on a set of data from a bicycle share. The focus was on differentiating how casual and member users make use of services in order to identify what casual users were best to target for conversion to membership.

View the report here.

Or a PDF of the report on the case study is available here.
